The course focuses on the economic development in Japan throughout the post-war period and discusses critical junctures and institutional change during the last decades, which influence current market trends and the recent economy in the whole region. Further, the EPA and SPA are discussed with the implications on trade relations between Europe and Japan.
The course connects knowledge on economic development and regional characteristics with specific cultural aspects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main objective of the course is to provide an overview on economic development in contemporary Japan and Japanese business culture, analyze Japanese economy while taking into account Asian regional markets and provide opportunities for practical skills in multi-cultural business environments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course the student: 1.	can explain the development and characteristics of economy in contemporary Japan; 2.	can analyse Japanese economy in broader Asian context; 3.	understands the background of EU-Japan economic and trade relations, knows main documents and developments; 4.	understands the Japanese business culture and is ready for communication with partners.
